00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:30,961
leave it for the judges to decide.

261
00:19:31,803 --> 00:19:36,638
I did ask the Principal
but my fears were laughed away.

262
00:19:37,309 --> 00:19:40,745
In the end, his "Shocking Anti-Theft Purse"

263
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:44,915
earned the award of excellence
in the Middle School finals.

264
00:19:49,121 --> 00:19:50,645
Shuya, Shuya, Shuya...

265
00:19:55,127 --> 00:19:56,594
Conclusion: Shuya Watanabe

266
00:19:56,795 --> 00:20:01,061
I asked him the truth about Manami's death.

267
00:20:12,945 --> 00:20:13,809
Just kidding...

268
00:20:15,514 --> 00:20:18,312
He discussed it quite happily.

269
00:20:18,717 --> 00:20:24,417
As if unaware the mother of
the murdered child was before him.

270
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:29,584
Student A's motivation for the killing

271
00:20:29,928 --> 00:20:32,089
was laughably simple.

272
00:20:32,931 --> 00:20:35,798
For the world to acknowledge his genius.

273
00:20:36,001 --> 00:20:39,095
He wanted acclaim as a superior person.

274
00:20:39,938 --> 00:20:44,671
However the day his science project
made the papers...

275
00:20:45,344 --> 00:20:48,336
it wasn't him who won the acclaim.

276
00:20:49,047 --> 00:20:52,112
(Middle School Girl Murders 4 Family Members)

277
00:20:52,147 --> 00:20:52,918
but another 13 year old.

278
00:20:52,918 --> 00:20:56,445
You win praise for doing good
but nobody really notices.

279
00:20:56,688 --> 00:20:59,657
That Lunacy thing was no big ideal.

280
00:21:00,859 --> 00:21:02,952
Why is Potassium Cyanide special?

281
00:21:03,228 --> 00:21:05,196
If it were me, every single thing...

282
00:21:05,530 --> 00:21:07,521
I'd create with my own hands.

283
00:21:08,033 --> 00:21:09,660
I want to kill him.

284
00:21:13,405 --> 00:21:17,102
That was exactly how I felt.

285
00:21:20,879 --> 00:21:24,246
Student B began school and started sports.

286
00:21:24,449 --> 00:21:27,316
But it was all strength-building
and he never got to hold a racket.

287
00:21:27,519 --> 00:21:29,646
Die, die, die, die.

288
00:21:29,855 --> 00:21:34,155
Though unhappy, he hadn't the courage to
talk to his course adviser.

289
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:39,595
He had his mom get him off sports
and started at cram school.

290
00:21:40,499 --> 00:21:43,832
His grades didn't improve and he started to worry

291
00:21:44,503 --> 00:21:46,403
but didn't work any harder.

292
00:21:53,378 --> 00:21:56,905
He made it to a police station and was held there,

293
00:21:57,783 --> 00:22:02,777
but was shocked when Mr. Tokura
came to pick him up.

294
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:05,320
Why isn't it Miss Moriguchi?

295
00:22:07,259 --> 00:22:08,385
Just shut up, idiot.

296
00:22:08,593 --> 00:22:10,823
Die, die, die...

297
00:22:11,897 --> 00:22:15,333
For breaking the rule against
entering video arcades,

298
00:22:15,534 --> 00:22:17,297
he was given a penalty.

299
00:22:18,904 --> 00:22:23,307
2 weeks cleaning poolside and the changing rooms.

300
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:27,008
He'd never have the balls to kill.

301
00:22:30,515 --> 00:22:34,747
I heard this a from Student B in his own home.

302
00:22:36,588 --> 00:22:41,389
His mother sat beside him.
Each time he spoke she'd say...

303
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:43,250
You poor thing...

304
00:22:44,129 --> 00:22:46,188
She said it time and again.

305
00:22:47,099 --> 00:22:50,193
Not about my dead daughter but about him.

306
00:22:54,306 --> 00:22:58,208
Around February, Student A made his approach to B,

307
00:22:59,111 --> 00:23:02,171
to lure him in to his dreadfull plan.

308
00:23:13,692 --> 00:23:15,592
I wonder who it can be?

309
00:23:18,029 --> 00:23:19,326
What?

310
00:23:20,932 --> 00:23:23,332
Is that the thing that won the prize?

311
00:23:23,802 --> 00:23:26,737
It's got more power now, so I want to test it out.

312
00:23:27,839 --> 00:23:32,606
Could be anyone, but the idea was to zap bad guys.

313
00:23:33,211 --> 00:23:34,906
Then let's test it on bad guys.

314
00:23:35,247 --> 00:23:38,273
Student B first suggested Mr. Tokura.

315
00:23:39,050 --> 00:23:41,143
Student A didn't respond.

316
00:23:42,754 --> 00:23:45,518
Then Student B put my name forward.

317
00:23:45,724 --> 00:23:46,918
It was just unforgiveable.

318
00:23:47,626 --> 00:23:51,926
Her own student in a tight spot yet
she sent a different teacher.

319
00:23:52,564 --> 00:23:54,828
She's already been a guinea-pig.

320
00:23:55,033 --> 00:23:57,934
Student A shot down that idea.

321
00:23:58,537 --> 00:24:01,005
How about her daughter?

322
00:24:02,174 --> 00:24:07,009
It'd teach her to put her kid
before the needs of her students.

323
00:24:07,746 --> 00:24:11,011
Student B described Manami's trips

324
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:14,749
to the pool to feed the dog.

325
00:24:15,687 --> 00:24:18,747
And about the purse she so wanted

326
00:24:19,124 --> 00:24:21,524
but I didn't buy her at the mall.

327
00:24:28,033 --> 00:24:29,694
The one they selected for their target,

328
00:24:30,535 --> 00:24:33,402
was the youngest and the weakest.

329
00:24:34,239 --> 00:24:36,139
It was my daughter.

330
00:24:50,789 --> 00:24:53,781
Your mom didn't buy you this, right?

331
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:57,091
Or did she, already?

332
00:24:58,763 --> 00:25:02,631
I thought so, because she told us
to get it for you.

333
00:25:02,901 --> 00:25:03,765
She did?

334
00:25:05,537 --> 00:25:08,700
A Valentine Day present from your lovely mom.

335
00:25:09,841 --> 00:25:10,967
Open it up,

336
00:25:11,543 --> 00:25:13,204
there's chocolate inside.

337
00:25:38,737 --> 00:25:42,332
What happened? She's not moving...

338
00:25:42,541 --> 00:25:43,906
She's dead.

339
00:25:44,109 --> 00:25:48,273
He was in a total panic... kicking up such a fuss.

340
00:25:48,613 --> 00:25:51,707
You can tell everyone it was me who did it.

341
00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:54,985
After I said that, I went home.

342
00:25:57,022 --> 00:25:58,250
Then that idiot...

343
00:26:03,495 --> 00:26:06,020
If they realized the purse killed her,

344
00:26:06,932 --> 00:26:09,298
suspicion would fall on me.

345
00:26:20,478 --> 00:26:22,673
So I figured I'd make it look like she fell.

346
00:26:26,751 --> 00:26:28,719
A spur of the moment decision.

347
00:26:51,643 --> 00:26:55,079
This is how Manami died.

348
00:27:10,729 --> 00:27:12,629
As I already told the 2 boys,

349
00:27:13,131 --> 00:27:18,296
If the police ruled it an accident
I won't rehash that verdict.

350
00:27:21,706 --> 00:27:22,832
But there is one thing.

351
00:27:23,041 --> 00:27:26,568
What killed her wasn't the purse.

352
00:27:30,048 --> 00:27:32,915
I had it thoroughly checked out.

353
00:27:33,118 --> 00:27:37,316
It's incapable of stopping
even a 4 year old's heart.

354
00:27:37,722 --> 00:27:39,781
It's a pathetic piece of work.

355
00:27:40,592 --> 00:27:41,923
Want to try it?

356
00:27:44,496 --> 00:27:48,489
Manami had simply fallen unconscious.

357
00:27:50,502 --> 00:27:53,471
She drowned after B threw her in.

358
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:57,403
That was the indisputable cause of Manami's death.

359
00:27:59,077 --> 00:28:00,510
It's so ironic.

360
00:28:01,479 --> 00:28:05,711
Student A had homicidal intent
but wasn't able to kill.

361
00:28:06,518 --> 00:28:11,820
Student B did not but brought about her death.

362
00:28:12,891 --> 00:28:14,756
Even if arraigned by the authorities,

363
00:28:14,959 --> 00:28:19,293
juvenile law would mandate
simple custodial supervision.

364
00:28:20,098 --> 00:28:22,157
Innocent to all intents and purposes.

365
00:28:23,134 --> 00:28:26,900
I judged that to be insufficient.

366
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:33,509
Teachers have a responsibility to
guide students back to the right path.

367
00:28:35,213 --> 00:28:40,515
I want them to admit their crime
and appreciate how precious life is.

368
00:28:41,686 --> 00:28:46,783
I want them to realize the gravity of their crime
and live with that burden.

369
00:28:51,096 --> 00:28:53,564
The milk that you all just drank...

370
00:28:54,299 --> 00:28:58,360
Two of them had something extra mixed in.

371
00:29:03,541 --> 00:29:08,240
The HIV-infected blood of Dr. Sakuramiya.

372
00:29:20,825 --> 00:29:22,224
Be quiet!

373
00:29:24,229 --> 00:29:27,130
You were both kind enough to drink it.

374
00:29:27,332 --> 00:29:28,299
Thank you.

375
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:32,497
Please be sure to get a blood test
in a couple of months.

376
00:29:32,804 --> 00:29:36,968
If it worked, you'll have
a 5-10 year incubation wait.

377
00:29:37,809 --> 00:29:39,777
Plenty of time I should think,

378
00:29:39,978 --> 00:29:43,345
to reflect on things and
appreciate the preciousness of life.

379
00:29:59,497 --> 00:30:00,555
Springtime...

380
00:30:01,032 --> 00:30:05,435
when the flowers, trees,
grass, birds, people, too...

381
00:30:05,737 --> 00:30:08,205
all blossom into life.

382
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:16,712
Every one of you,

383
00:30:18,049 --> 00:30:20,540
please have a meaningfull spring break.

384
00:30:21,719 --> 00:30:23,084
(Yuko Moriguchi's Confession)

385
00:30:23,288 --> 00:30:24,880
That's the end.

386
00:31:13,271 --> 00:31:14,932
Miss Yuko...

387
00:31:16,474 --> 00:31:18,738
Can you believe it?

388
00:31:21,346 --> 00:31:25,646
After you left and the new term started,

389
00:31:29,287 --> 00:31:32,347
our class could be this full of smilling faces?

390
00:31:33,458 --> 00:31:35,255
(6th April - 8th Grade, Class B)(Start of term)

391
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:40,989
April... suddenly it's 8th grade
and there's a new homeroom teacher.

392
00:31:41,199 --> 00:31:45,101
Wer-ther has been my nickname since school.

393
00:31:47,038 --> 00:31:49,097
Doesn't mean I spend my days in sorrow!

394
00:31:49,307 --> 00:31:51,502
His jokes aren't funny.

395
00:31:54,045 --> 00:31:55,842
too pally from day one.

396
00:31:56,047 --> 00:31:57,241
Hayakawa?

397
00:31:57,682 --> 00:31:58,944
And Naoki?

398
00:31:59,217 --> 00:32:01,583
Absent again with a cold.

399
00:32:01,786 --> 00:32:05,313
We all knew he wasn't ill at all.

400
00:32:06,090 --> 00:32:08,524
What surprised us more,

401
00:32:09,327 --> 00:32:12,990
was that Shuya was at school at all.

402
00:32:13,197 --> 00:32:16,462
I wasn't a good student back in my schooldays.

403
00:32:17,001 --> 00:32:21,563
But one particular book by
one particular man changed my life.

404
00:32:24,309 --> 00:32:26,277
That wasn't just unfunny,

405
00:32:28,212 --> 00:32:30,009
it was a cruel joke.

406
00:32:31,316 --> 00:32:35,548
"As I wandered the globe
I began to read the Bible. "

407
00:32:36,354 --> 00:32:40,347
"In it, I glimpsed the true nature of education. "

408
00:32:41,759 --> 00:32:43,989
"Though a man might have 100 sheep,"

409
00:32:44,629 --> 00:32:46,221
"should just 1 go astray,"

410
00:32:47,098 --> 00:32:49,362
"in order to save that 1, the man,"

411
00:32:50,501 --> 00:32:54,335
"even though he risk the 99 others... "

412
00:32:54,639 --> 00:32:56,038
Sir, you're the best!

413
00:33:01,079 --> 00:33:04,173
I just want to be totallly open with you all.

414
00:33:04,916 --> 00:33:07,749
They're just a bunch of wimps.

415
00:33:08,019 --> 00:33:10,317
Whatever your problem, come to me.

416
00:33:11,823 --> 00:33:15,190
Everyone was desperate to
escape the truth you thrust at us.

417
00:33:15,393 --> 00:33:16,917
I'll hand whatever you throw at me!

418
00:33:19,564 --> 00:33:22,226
They're all pretending to be idiots.

419
00:33:22,433 --> 00:33:25,561
I want to be an elder brother to you all!

420
00:33:27,905 --> 00:33:31,306
(Mizuki Kitahara's Confession)

421
00:33:31,509 --> 00:33:34,842
(Dr. M. Sakuramiya)

422
00:33:36,781 --> 00:33:37,372
"Miyu"?

423
00:33:37,915 --> 00:33:38,939
"Natsky"?

424
00:33:39,250 --> 00:33:40,114
"Sugi-June"?

425
00:33:40,385 --> 00:33:41,443
"Missa-Pon"?

426
00:34:03,508 --> 00:34:04,406
I'm sorry.

427
00:34:08,513 --> 00:34:09,912
I've been lying.

428
00:34:10,982 --> 00:34:14,645
Naoki's not absent because of illness.

429
00:34:15,086 --> 00:34:17,281
But he's not skipping school.

430
00:34:17,488 --> 00:34:20,946
He wants to come but a mental issue prevents him.

431
00:34:21,159 --> 00:34:26,256
The only person in class who
doesn't know the reason is Werther himself.

432
00:34:26,464 --> 00:34:28,397
<i>Anyone leaks teacher's confession
we'll treat you as "Student C".</i>

433
00:34:28,497 --> 00:34:31,397
We all got that anonymous text

434
00:34:32,603 --> 00:34:34,730
right after the end of the previous term.

435
00:34:34,939 --> 00:34:39,035
How about we try to make a nice
atmosphere for Naoki's return?

436
00:34:43,581 --> 00:34:47,642
Okay, say we take turns making notes,

437
00:34:47,852 --> 00:34:51,913
then once a week, student chair Mizuki and I,
deliver them?

438
00:34:53,057 --> 00:34:55,116
What do you think, Mizuki?

439
00:34:59,163 --> 00:34:59,925
Thank you.

440
00:35:00,198 --> 00:35:01,995
Mizuki, don't you have a nickname?

441
00:35:02,667 --> 00:35:03,497
Me-the-hoe...

442
00:35:04,902 --> 00:35:09,669
I was called that in Elementalry School.

443
00:35:09,907 --> 00:35:10,771
Me-the-hoe!

444
00:35:10,975 --> 00:35:12,067
Me-the-hoe.

445
00:35:13,277 --> 00:35:14,904
Like the name, "Mizuho".

446
00:35:16,013 --> 00:35:19,779
Mizuho huh? I'll call you that from now on.

447
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:23,778
Me-the-hoe...

448
00:35:24,956 --> 00:35:25,820
Louder, louder!

449
00:35:26,557 --> 00:35:29,685
Me-the-hoe, Me-the-hoe...

450
00:35:51,382 --> 00:35:52,747
Where's Naoki?

451
00:35:58,890 --> 00:36:01,791
If only his other teacher had been
as enthusiastic as you,

452
00:36:01,993 --> 00:36:05,258
maybe Naoki would've escaped
this mental issue he has.

453
00:36:05,630 --> 00:36:09,532
That lady, she was a single mother, right?

454
00:36:10,201 --> 00:36:13,193
Bringing her own child to work,
in the first place...

455
00:36:13,404 --> 00:36:19,070
To avoid talking about the incident,
she kept criticizing Miss Yuko.

456
00:36:20,244 --> 00:36:25,614
She was so caught up in her own child
she'd no time for her students.

457
00:36:25,816 --> 00:36:27,283
- If I might say...
- poor Naoki...

458
00:36:27,718 --> 00:36:31,279
If he puts his mind to it, he can do anything.

459
00:36:31,689 --> 00:36:34,214
Trust me with your son, please.

460
00:36:34,425 --> 00:36:36,017
Thank you very much.

461
00:36:40,498 --> 00:36:41,760
Darling...

462
00:36:47,939 --> 00:36:50,373
Mind your own business!

463
00:36:59,150 --> 00:37:01,175
It's all that woman's fault.

464
00:37:01,385 --> 00:37:02,477
(Yuko Shimomura's Confession)

465
00:37:03,721 --> 00:37:07,555
That my lovely Naoki turned into this...

466
00:37:07,758 --> 00:37:09,020
I'm taking a piss.

467
00:37:10,595 --> 00:37:16,090
He hates us touching anything he's made dirty.

468
00:37:16,434 --> 00:37:19,892
He cleans everything incessantly.

469
00:37:25,343 --> 00:37:26,367
Yet for all that,

470
00:37:27,712 --> 00:37:29,043
he doesn't wash his hair,

471
00:37:30,948 --> 00:37:32,006
nor take a bath.

472
00:37:34,418 --> 00:37:35,442
That bitch...

473
00:37:35,686 --> 00:37:37,017
Why Manami?

474
00:37:37,688 --> 00:37:40,248
Why did she have to die?

475
00:37:40,458 --> 00:37:42,016
What are you suggesting?

476
00:37:42,226 --> 00:37:46,253
As if it were Naoki's fault the daughter died.

477
00:37:47,732 --> 00:37:54,194
He was just tricked into helping by a bad friend.

478
00:37:54,405 --> 00:37:56,202
You poor thing.

479
00:37:58,309 --> 00:37:59,674
Darling...

480
00:38:02,246 --> 00:38:03,076
Get away!

481
00:38:26,671 --> 00:38:28,571
You don't regret a thing, do you?

482
00:38:49,026 --> 00:38:51,460
Shuya Watanabe - Die

483
00:38:59,870 --> 00:39:00,859
Murderer

484
00:39:01,072 --> 00:39:02,369
12 points, 8 points

485
00:39:04,241 --> 00:39:06,368
Die murderer

486
00:39:06,577 --> 00:39:08,511
Maekawa adds 2 points

487
00:39:21,492 --> 00:39:23,289
Rack up "Punish-Him Points"

488
00:39:43,013 --> 00:39:44,844
This text went to everybody.

489
00:39:45,049 --> 00:39:46,812
The murderer's come-uppance measured in points

490
00:39:47,485 --> 00:39:49,248
Of course it was anonymous.

491
00:39:55,593 --> 00:39:58,084
Who'll write some kind words to Naoki?

492
00:40:31,729 --> 00:40:34,129
K is for...

493
00:40:34,331 --> 00:40:35,195
"Keep smilling"!

494
00:40:35,399 --> 00:40:36,525
I is for...

495
00:40:36,734 --> 00:40:38,599
"it's better to share"!

496
00:40:38,803 --> 00:40:40,600
L is for...

497
00:40:40,805 --> 00:40:43,000
"Life can be hard"!

498
00:40:43,207 --> 00:40:44,105
L is for...

499
00:40:44,308 --> 00:40:46,173
"Let's be happy"!

500
00:40:47,812 --> 00:40:49,609
How's he coming along?

501
00:40:49,814 --> 00:40:51,372
Could I just have a word?

502
00:41:01,826 --> 00:41:03,157
Sir...

503
00:41:04,695 --> 00:41:05,992
Call me Werther.

504
00:41:07,031 --> 00:41:10,762
Even if we keep this up, Naoki's never coming back.

505
00:41:11,068 --> 00:41:12,262
I think this makes it worse.

506
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:15,439
Mizuho, we're at a crucial point now.

507
00:41:15,639 --> 00:41:18,506
Overcome and we'll see the light.

508
00:41:21,178 --> 00:41:22,907
E is "Everyone's waiting"

509
00:41:23,747 --> 00:41:25,715
R is "Return to us soon"!

510
00:41:36,994 --> 00:41:38,461
Why is it?

511
00:41:39,463 --> 00:41:41,454
My good boy, Naoki...

512
00:41:41,665 --> 00:41:43,997
every time they show up,

513
00:41:46,036 --> 00:41:48,004
he gets so upset.

514
00:41:51,475 --> 00:41:52,567
That stupid teacher,

515
00:41:54,545 --> 00:41:56,740
spouting his fancy words,

516
00:41:59,583 --> 00:42:01,608
yet doing no good at all.

517
00:42:09,226 --> 00:42:11,751
I put a sleeping pill in his lunch.

518
00:42:16,033 --> 00:42:18,695
My husband's always away at work.

519
00:42:19,236 --> 00:42:22,034
My daughter's busy at college in Tokyo.

520
00:42:23,140 --> 00:42:24,698
As the only one here.

521
00:42:26,176 --> 00:42:28,371
I'm all that child has.

522
