Someone who wouldn't guess my real thinking.

796
01:09:05,641 --> 01:09:07,768
Who would do as I say,

797
01:09:08,544 --> 01:09:13,004
then blurt out my crime to the entire world.

798
01:09:13,749 --> 01:09:15,512
A true idiot among idiots.

799
01:09:16,785 --> 01:09:17,774
There he was.

800
01:09:22,057 --> 01:09:25,117
You can tell everyone it was me who did it.

801
01:09:29,698 --> 01:09:31,689
Don't worry, you're not an accomplice.

802
01:09:32,635 --> 01:09:34,660
You were never my equal.

803
01:09:36,138 --> 01:09:38,470
you're a dumb-ass wimp.

804
01:09:38,974 --> 01:09:41,238
It's obvious you're a failure.

805
01:09:41,744 --> 01:09:44,235
I just told him the truth...

806
01:09:44,713 --> 01:09:47,011
Why did he have to do that?

807
01:09:47,216 --> 01:09:49,183
4 Year Old Drowns After Fall Into Pool

808
01:09:49,552 --> 01:09:50,484
Why did he butt in?

809
01:09:51,820 --> 01:09:53,947
I wanted to be your friend.

810
01:09:54,323 --> 01:09:55,051
I just...

811
01:09:55,791 --> 01:09:56,815
with you...

812
01:09:58,561 --> 01:09:59,892
I didn't have anyone.

813
01:10:00,563 --> 01:10:02,531
Want to come watch movies?

814
01:10:03,065 --> 01:10:05,499
I always wanted to talk to you.

815
01:10:05,701 --> 01:10:07,931
To think someone noticed me...

816
01:10:08,137 --> 01:10:10,230
You're different from those jerks.

817
01:10:10,806 --> 01:10:13,775
You seem relaxed... grown-up.

818
01:10:14,109 --> 01:10:17,237
Someone acknowledged me.

819
01:10:17,446 --> 01:10:20,472
So I chose a target, as you asked.

820
01:10:21,016 --> 01:10:22,483
How about her daughter?

821
01:10:22,685 --> 01:10:23,709
Why Manami?

822
01:10:24,186 --> 01:10:26,381
Why did she have to die?

823
01:10:26,622 --> 01:10:27,850
I wonder why?

824
01:10:28,157 --> 01:10:29,715
I've forgotten it now.

825
01:10:30,025 --> 01:10:31,515
I just did as I was told.

826
01:10:33,162 --> 01:10:35,153
I even surveyed the scene first.

827
01:10:36,332 --> 01:10:37,264
But then you...

828
01:10:37,466 --> 01:10:40,026
You can tell everyone it was me who did it.

829
01:10:40,236 --> 01:10:40,998
That jerk...

830
01:10:44,373 --> 01:10:46,933
He so wanted to be a murderer.

831
01:10:48,244 --> 01:10:49,211
But he couldn't do it.

832
01:10:49,979 --> 01:10:51,606
The kid was still alive.

833
01:10:51,947 --> 01:10:53,209
She was breathing properly.

834
01:10:54,383 --> 01:10:55,680
It's obvious you're a failure.

835
01:10:57,419 --> 01:10:58,818
A failure, huh?

836
01:10:59,388 --> 01:11:01,913
He wanted to kill but couldn't.

837
01:11:02,124 --> 01:11:03,216
He's the damn failure.

838
01:11:03,425 --> 01:11:04,619
Look who's talking.

839
01:11:04,827 --> 01:11:08,524
I managed to achieve

840
01:11:08,931 --> 01:11:10,694
what he couldn't.

841
01:11:14,536 --> 01:11:16,026
Why did you butt in?

842
01:11:16,805 --> 01:11:18,796
If you want to tell the world, feel free.

843
01:11:27,182 --> 01:11:28,149
Pop.

844
01:11:28,350 --> 01:11:32,047
After a month that idiot teacher finally twigged.

845
01:11:32,254 --> 01:11:36,247
I don't intend to rehash the police verdict.

846
01:11:36,458 --> 01:11:37,482
Damn it.

847
01:11:37,860 --> 01:11:41,057
What killed her wasn't the purse.

848
01:11:41,597 --> 01:11:46,091
It's incapable of stopping
even a 4 year old's heart.

849
01:11:46,302 --> 01:11:47,132
It sucks.

850
01:11:47,636 --> 01:11:51,333
Two of them had something extra mixed in.

851
01:11:52,508 --> 01:11:54,738
The HIV- infected blood of Dr. Sakuramiya.

852
01:12:07,489 --> 01:12:09,616
That was perfect, Moriguchi!

853
01:12:13,429 --> 01:12:14,487
A deadly disease...

854
01:12:14,930 --> 01:12:17,160
Perfect... if I contract that,

855
01:12:17,366 --> 01:12:20,597
Dad would surely have to tell Mom.

856
01:12:21,503 --> 01:12:23,494
He'd have to let me see her.

857
01:12:24,073 --> 01:12:27,099
Actually, she'd move mountains to come find me.

858
01:12:27,776 --> 01:12:30,540
We're reconciled, she looks after me...

859
01:12:31,413 --> 01:12:34,007
A perfect testament to my genius.

860
01:12:38,320 --> 01:12:39,514
Pop.

861
01:12:41,690 --> 01:12:45,353
After that, I was just killing time.

862
01:12:49,565 --> 01:12:50,930
The smilling...

863
01:12:51,133 --> 01:12:51,929
The tears...

864
01:12:52,835 --> 01:12:54,427
All of it... that, too.

865
01:12:55,003 --> 01:12:56,868
Everything... life itself.

866
01:13:00,709 --> 01:13:02,370
Just meaningless...

867
01:13:03,879 --> 01:13:05,278
...a waste of time.

868
01:13:10,886 --> 01:13:14,083
I saw you by chance that day...

869
01:13:16,925 --> 01:13:18,392
Why did he do that?

870
01:13:19,361 --> 01:13:20,521
The retard.

871
01:13:21,497 --> 01:13:24,864
The one I considered a failure.

872
01:13:29,638 --> 01:13:31,196
It was Moriguchi's fault.

873
01:13:31,740 --> 01:13:33,731
She was trying to kill me.

874
01:13:34,610 --> 01:13:36,908
She even sent a spy to my home.

875
01:13:37,112 --> 01:13:40,240
Yet my mum kept bad-mouthing her to him.

876
01:13:40,449 --> 01:13:41,882
That's why she was killed.

877
01:13:43,285 --> 01:13:46,015
I desperately tried to stop her getting infected.

878
01:13:46,221 --> 01:13:48,348
To prevent her dying.

879
01:13:48,557 --> 01:13:49,888
I was going to be killed, too.

880
01:13:54,997 --> 01:13:56,259
I mean...

881
01:13:57,132 --> 01:13:58,895
Am I even alive?

882
01:14:01,771 --> 01:14:03,504
(Naoki Shimomura's confession)

883
01:14:03,539 --> 01:14:05,637
It certainly doesn't feel like it.

884
01:14:09,344 --> 01:14:10,106
I stink.

885
01:14:10,446 --> 01:14:13,006
But it's proof I'm alive.

886
01:14:13,215 --> 01:14:16,548
This hair, my nails, the dandruff, the stench...

887
01:14:16,752 --> 01:14:18,811
Being hungry... all proof I'm alive.

888
01:14:30,632 --> 01:14:33,032
I'm dying... I'm dying!

889
01:14:35,270 --> 01:14:36,066
I'm dying.

890
01:14:36,271 --> 01:14:37,260
At the age of just 13.

891
01:14:37,639 --> 01:14:39,072
Moriguchi's killing me.

892
01:14:39,274 --> 01:14:40,104
I've never kissed,

893
01:14:41,109 --> 01:14:41,803
or made out,

894
01:14:42,010 --> 01:14:43,602
or done anything.

895
01:14:44,613 --> 01:14:45,375
Why?

896
01:14:46,114 --> 01:14:47,479
You're such a failure.

897
01:14:47,683 --> 01:14:48,809
No, I'm not!

898
01:14:49,284 --> 01:14:50,012
I'm...

899
01:14:50,219 --> 01:14:51,811
Naoki, you're a good boy.

900
01:14:52,020 --> 01:14:53,282
Aren't I, Mom?

901
01:14:53,489 --> 01:14:55,548
Good at sport, at studying...

902
01:14:56,458 --> 01:14:57,948
At killing...

903
01:14:59,261 --> 01:15:00,819
You can succeed if you try.

904
01:15:13,242 --> 01:15:15,176
I'm so sorry, darling...

905
01:15:16,178 --> 01:15:16,974
Why?

906
01:15:18,347 --> 01:15:19,780
'Cause you're a failure.

907
01:15:19,982 --> 01:15:21,643
Shut up!

908
01:15:25,220 --> 01:15:26,517
I'm sorry.

909
01:15:27,422 --> 01:15:28,912
Your poor mom,

910
01:15:29,358 --> 01:15:32,156
she didn't bring you up right.

911
01:15:32,361 --> 01:15:33,191
Failure.

912
01:15:52,848 --> 01:15:54,611
According to his lawyer,

913
01:15:54,816 --> 01:15:59,276
the child apparently received
the court's verdict calmly.

914
01:15:59,888 --> 01:16:03,289
Miss, about "life"...

915
01:16:05,661 --> 01:16:07,288
To think how much he loved his mom...

916
01:16:08,530 --> 01:16:09,292
Silly jerk.

917
01:16:10,899 --> 01:16:11,957
Look who's talking.

918
01:16:15,037 --> 01:16:16,402
Nothing.

919
01:16:18,240 --> 01:16:19,172
What do you mean by that?

920
01:16:20,175 --> 01:16:20,869
You're being scary.

921
01:16:21,076 --> 01:16:22,600
What the hell do you know?

922
01:16:26,715 --> 01:16:29,684
I know everything about you.

923
01:16:32,588 --> 01:16:36,422
You were just a way to kill time.

924
01:16:38,694 --> 01:16:39,820
But I was through.

925
01:16:40,796 --> 01:16:43,390
I'm sick of that "Lunacy" crap.

926
01:16:43,599 --> 01:16:47,057
And your longing to be like her.

927
01:16:47,402 --> 01:16:49,063
Collecting crap like this...

928
01:16:52,107 --> 01:16:53,768
You identify with Lunacy?

929
01:16:53,976 --> 01:16:57,537
You're just a wannabe, dreaming little dreams.

930
01:16:58,814 --> 01:16:59,803
You're an idiot.

931
01:17:00,015 --> 01:17:00,674
Shuya...

932
01:17:02,250 --> 01:17:04,275
You haven't got the courage to kill.

933
01:17:04,720 --> 01:17:07,780
Why not drink this and make a start?

934
01:17:14,196 --> 01:17:15,288
Mother complex.

935
01:17:17,132 --> 01:17:18,759
That's all you are.

936
01:17:20,235 --> 01:17:24,695
Hung up on a mother who abandoned you.

937
01:17:24,906 --> 01:17:26,703
Yet without the balls to go see her.

938
01:17:28,076 --> 01:17:31,341
Scared in case she rejects you, right?

939
01:17:31,546 --> 01:17:33,844
You know full well she abandoned you.

940
01:17:44,626 --> 01:17:46,059
Miss...

941
01:17:47,396 --> 01:17:51,025
I saw you by chance that day...

942
01:17:54,936 --> 01:17:56,335
I did.

943
01:18:30,672 --> 01:18:32,537
You didn't add anything, did you?

944
01:18:34,076 --> 01:18:36,169
I mean put blood in the milk.

945
01:18:38,046 --> 01:18:40,014
You'd never do that.

946
01:18:41,083 --> 01:18:42,516
So I always thought.

947
01:18:43,518 --> 01:18:45,782
Now I don't know anymore.

948
01:18:47,756 --> 01:18:49,849
Now I don't care if Werther dies.

949
01:18:50,058 --> 01:18:54,222
It seems Mr. Terada's taking time off school.

950
01:18:55,363 --> 01:18:58,230
Since Shimomura turned out like that.

951
01:18:58,667 --> 01:19:01,465
But it was Werther's fault...

952
01:19:01,670 --> 01:19:02,898
It was my fault.

953
01:19:04,272 --> 01:19:07,639
I'd meet up with him occasionally.

954
01:19:07,843 --> 01:19:09,367
He was so enthusiastic...

955
01:19:09,745 --> 01:19:11,372
...so pure-hearted...

956
01:19:11,913 --> 01:19:14,347
Such a Sakuramiya devotee.

957
01:19:15,884 --> 01:19:20,878
So I confessed the fact Sakuramiya
was Manami's father.

958
01:19:23,258 --> 01:19:26,056
I reeled him in and used him...

959
01:19:26,394 --> 01:19:28,487
to corner those boys.

960
01:19:33,568 --> 01:19:36,867
Of course I didn't tell him how Manami died.

961
01:19:37,139 --> 01:19:39,972
He listened to my advice so carefully.

962
01:19:40,542 --> 01:19:42,533
About home visits to Shimomura...

963
01:19:43,111 --> 01:19:47,673
"No matter how unpopular keep at it,
at least once a week... "

964
01:19:48,517 --> 01:19:51,111
"If the door's shut in your face, keep calling. "

965
01:19:51,720 --> 01:19:54,188
"Sakuramiya would do no less. "

966
01:19:55,290 --> 01:19:57,588
That's what I kept telling him.

967
01:19:59,895 --> 01:20:03,058
When he asked me about Watanabe's bullying,

968
01:20:04,065 --> 01:20:07,034
I told him to claim a student had reported it,

969
01:20:07,235 --> 01:20:09,726
to help bring it home to them.

970
01:20:11,773 --> 01:20:16,608
Knowing full well it'd promote further bullying.

971
01:20:18,046 --> 01:20:20,071
I said it on purpose.

972
01:20:21,983 --> 01:20:25,077
I was disappointed to hear it'd stopped.

973
01:20:25,821 --> 01:20:28,255
I counted on the cruelty of the class

974
01:20:28,824 --> 01:20:32,225
to result in his death or suicide.

975
01:20:33,361 --> 01:20:35,955
You guys were kinder than I thought.

976
01:20:36,164 --> 01:20:37,290
Miss...

977
01:20:39,901 --> 01:20:41,266
This is for you.

978
01:20:41,469 --> 01:20:42,595
Thank you.

979
01:20:51,112 --> 01:20:53,603
As to blood in their milk...

980
01:20:57,052 --> 01:20:59,748
"Don't repay hatred with hatred. "

981
01:21:01,289 --> 01:21:04,816
"That'll never bring peace of mind. "

982
01:21:06,528 --> 01:21:08,996
"Someday they'll be reformed. "

983
01:21:09,297 --> 01:21:11,060
"Believe in them. "

984
01:21:11,266 --> 01:21:15,635
"That'll bring your salvation, too. "

985
01:21:16,972 --> 01:21:19,133
That's what Sakuramiya said.

986
01:21:20,141 --> 01:21:20,971
To the very end,

987
01:21:22,377 --> 01:21:25,403
he kept saying the right thing.

988
01:21:26,882 --> 01:21:28,509
Whereas I...

989
01:21:32,621 --> 01:21:35,784
went ahead and told them anyway.

990
01:21:45,767 --> 01:21:48,395
But even if I'd actually done it.

991
01:21:49,037 --> 01:21:51,232
the chance of infection's practically zero.

992
01:21:55,010 --> 01:21:57,740
Even if you get AIDS,

993
01:21:58,046 --> 01:22:00,810
it's not a death sentence now.

994
01:22:01,750 --> 01:22:04,412
Drugs can ward off the disease.

995
01:22:05,854 --> 01:22:07,446
With Sakuramiya,

996
01:22:08,757 --> 01:22:13,592
if we'd found the cancer earlier,
he wouldn't have died.

997
01:22:16,865 --> 01:22:18,799
But you all had no idea...

998
01:22:20,568 --> 01:22:22,627
You quaked at the mention of HIV.

999
01:22:24,372 --> 01:22:26,465
So pathetic and clueless...

1000
01:22:34,883 --> 01:22:36,111
Miss...

1001
01:22:39,788 --> 01:22:42,313
I lost my family.

1002
01:22:45,060 --> 01:22:46,527
And Shuya...

1003
01:22:53,101 --> 01:22:54,693
I'll never forgive.

1004
01:22:57,005 --> 01:22:57,994
So?

1005
01:22:58,673 --> 01:23:01,073
Do you think I should die?

1006
01:23:01,476 --> 01:23:02,807
You don't understand.

1007
01:23:09,317 --> 01:23:11,785
Shuya's just lonely.

1008
01:23:12,253 --> 01:23:13,720
He just wants to be noticed...

1009
01:23:14,055 --> 01:23:15,113
...by his mother.

1010
01:23:17,258 --> 01:23:18,520
Because she left...

1011
01:23:18,960 --> 01:23:20,928
'Cause his mom abandoned him...

1012
01:23:21,262 --> 01:23:24,663
he just needs recognition and...

1013
01:23:50,091 --> 01:23:51,353
Miss...

1014
01:23:53,428 --> 01:23:54,986
About life...

1015
01:23:57,298 --> 01:23:59,198
It's no big deal.

1016
01:26:04,159 --> 01:26:05,990
It's all so stupid.

1017
01:26:15,570 --> 01:26:17,299
She was still warm.

1018
01:26:18,006 --> 01:26:22,238
It was so creepy, I put the body in the fridge.

1019
01:26:24,245 --> 01:26:26,839
It's just a minor committing murder.

1020
01:26:27,115 --> 01:26:29,379
The juvenile penal code will protect me.

1021
01:26:29,918 --> 01:26:31,579
I won't get the death sentence.

1022
01:26:33,588 --> 01:26:34,555
What a let-down.

1023
01:26:36,157 --> 01:26:40,924
When I began building,
I wasn't sure how I'd use it.

1024
01:26:41,896 --> 01:26:42,590
Three days ago.

1025
01:26:42,797 --> 01:26:44,264
Associate Professor Yasaka

1026
01:26:44,465 --> 01:26:49,027
It was from my mother,
saying she wanted to meet.

1027
01:26:50,972 --> 01:26:54,169
Without a second thought,
I headed for her university.

1028
01:26:55,009 --> 01:26:59,173
Department of Science & Engineering,
Electrical Engineering Lab 3...

1029
01:27:01,649 --> 01:27:04,914
I saw her, just beyond the door.

1030
01:27:05,987 --> 01:27:08,581
If I'd just call out, tears would flow,

1031
01:27:09,591 --> 01:27:11,650
and she'd hug me to her.

1032
01:27:12,594 --> 01:27:13,583
But...

1033
01:27:15,129 --> 01:27:16,721
just then I had a realization.

1034
01:27:17,699 --> 01:27:21,931
What I wanted her to embrace,
wasn't this body of mine,

1035
01:27:22,971 --> 01:27:24,097
but something bigger,

1036
01:27:25,073 --> 01:27:27,439
my talent and...

1037
01:27:28,309 --> 01:27:31,039
...the great exploit I'd leave behind.

1038
01:27:31,980 --> 01:27:33,675
I walked away from the university.

1039
01:27:34,515 --> 01:27:36,346
In order to leave my mark on the world,

1040
01:27:38,553 --> 01:27:41,044
I'd found a use for my bomb.

1041
01:27:42,824 --> 01:27:44,689
The imminent mass murder,

1042
01:27:45,126 --> 01:27:48,653
won't have some idiot like
Shimomura for a witness,

1043
01:27:49,430 --> 01:27:52,490
but all of you who gather on this site.

1044
01:27:55,169 --> 01:27:57,364
The historical events of tomorrow,

1045
01:27:59,574 --> 01:28:00,632
my death too,

1046
01:28:01,409 --> 01:28:02,933
must be vouched for,

1047
01:28:03,711 --> 01:28:06,077
and my desires recorded,

1048
01:28:07,982 --> 01:28:11,076
for the benefit of my mother.

1049
01:28:21,763 --> 01:28:26,325
In this world, there are people
who can be forgiven for murder.

1050
01:28:27,168 --> 01:28:27,998
For them...

1051
01:28:29,570 --> 01:28:30,127
...for me, too.

1052
01:28:30,838 --> 01:28:32,999
...to build a better, new world,

1053
01:28:33,441 --> 01:28:36,205
there is a right to overstep certain obstacles.

1054
01:28:37,178 --> 01:28:40,739
That's what the hero of "Crime and Punishment"

1055
01:28:40,948 --> 01:28:44,406
Raskolnikov says before he kills the old woman.

1056
01:28:45,787 --> 01:28:47,414
But what I want to say is

1057
01:28:47,989 --> 01:28:48,614
that life...

1058
01:28:49,357 --> 01:28:50,619
every life... is precious,

1059
01:28:52,160 --> 01:28:54,287
every life is beautiful,

1060
01:28:55,296 --> 01:28:59,562
and in this world of ours,
every life has equal value!

1061
01:29:08,242 --> 01:29:09,709
Just kidding...

1062
01:29:58,192 --> 01:30:02,822
Darling, it's Mommy. Sorry you've been so lonely.

1063
01:30:03,030 --> 01:30:04,088
Who is this?

1064
01:30:05,199 --> 01:30:06,393
Long time, no see.

1065
01:30:06,601 --> 01:30:07,499
It's Moriguchi.

1066
01:30:08,169 --> 01:30:10,569
I have your bomb.

1067
01:30:11,005 --> 01:30:14,304
A simple thing put together by a simple mind.

1068
01:30:14,575 --> 01:30:16,702
It was a cinch to disarm.

1069
01:30:17,245 --> 01:30:19,304
You blabbered on the website...

1070
01:30:19,514 --> 01:30:20,208
Shut up!

1071
01:30:20,415 --> 01:30:21,177
No, I won't.

1072
01:30:22,683 --> 01:30:24,981
I want to discuss my revenge.

1073
01:30:25,420 --> 01:30:27,217
Simply killing you,

1074
01:30:27,789 --> 01:30:31,225
won't result in you despising your life.

1075
01:30:31,559 --> 01:30:32,526
Rather than murder.

1076
01:30:33,027 --> 01:30:37,259
I kept checking your website for a better idea.

1077
01:30:38,166 --> 01:30:42,398
Then I saw it, your ode to your mother.

1078
01:30:43,304 --> 01:30:44,737
But lying is wrong.

1079
01:30:46,140 --> 01:30:50,804
As your former teacher,
I must correct your mistruths.

1080
01:30:51,679 --> 01:30:54,614
The e-mail with your mother's address.

1081
01:30:55,583 --> 01:30:58,074
Did you think that was from her?

1082
01:30:58,286 --> 01:30:59,184
Mother...

1083
01:31:00,822 --> 01:31:04,087
You sure hurried over there the next day.

1084
01:31:04,292 --> 01:31:07,125
I saw her, just beyond the door.

1085
01:31:07,328 --> 01:31:09,558
Actually, you left without seeing her.

1086
01:31:09,797 --> 01:31:11,822
In order to leave my mark on the world.

1087
01:31:12,800 --> 01:31:14,791
How could you lie like that?

1088
01:31:15,703 --> 01:31:16,897
You bitch.

1089
01:31:17,104 --> 01:31:19,902
You crept into her research lab,

1090
01:31:20,107 --> 01:31:25,977
clutching your crappy inventions
in the hope she'd take a look.

1091
01:31:26,914 --> 01:31:30,315
But she wasn't to be found.

1092
01:31:30,818 --> 01:31:33,651
Ain't that right, kiddo?

1093
01:31:40,595 --> 01:31:41,653
Hey.

1094
01:31:42,597 --> 01:31:43,894
What do you want?

1095
01:31:45,199 --> 01:31:48,999
This is Associate Professor Yasaka, right?

1096
01:31:50,137 --> 01:31:51,126
Do you know her?

1097
01:31:51,639 --> 01:31:54,403
The person I admire most in the world.

1098
01:31:55,276 --> 01:31:58,871
Yes, but her name's, Seguchi, now.

1099
01:31:59,213 --> 01:31:59,907
Seguchi?

1100
01:32:00,114 --> 01:32:03,675
These guys are on their honeymoon right now.

1101
01:32:04,185 --> 01:32:07,814
Amazing at their age... a shotgun marriage.

1102
01:32:08,155 --> 01:32:12,558
You chucked everything and
ran out of there, bawling.

1103
01:32:14,161 --> 01:32:15,219
Impressed that I know?

1104
01:32:15,930 --> 01:32:17,659
I was watching.

1105
01:32:20,034 --> 01:32:25,165
It was me who sent you
the address of her workplace.

1106
01:32:27,308 --> 01:32:28,605
Miss Kitahara,

1107
01:32:29,443 --> 01:32:31,604
the girl you killed,

1108
01:32:31,812 --> 01:32:34,280
she told me your one weakness.

1109
01:32:35,283 --> 01:32:37,080
Shuya's just lonely.

1110
01:32:37,852 --> 01:32:39,820
He just wants to be noticed,

1111
01:32:40,688 --> 01:32:41,882
by his mother.

1112
01:32:42,690 --> 01:32:43,850
I did some research.

1113
01:32:44,759 --> 01:32:46,727
It was easy to get the whereabouts,

1114
01:32:46,961 --> 01:32:50,658
of the woman you'd commit murder
to have notice you.

1115
01:32:50,865 --> 01:32:53,493
And to find out who she's with.

1116
01:32:53,701 --> 01:32:54,360
Shut up!

1117
01:32:57,538 --> 01:33:03,238
I wanted to check the extent of
your feelings with my own eyes.

1118
01:33:06,380 --> 01:33:11,113
After acting so cool, you were in a total mess.

1119
01:33:12,153 --> 01:33:13,381
Just then I had a realization...

1120
01:33:13,955 --> 01:33:16,355
That you'd been abandoned...

1121
01:33:16,557 --> 01:33:18,991
Worse, you'd been totally forgotten.

1122
01:33:19,193 --> 01:33:20,660
I walked away from the university.

1123
01:33:20,861 --> 01:33:24,888
Total despair. Time to die without more ado,

1124
01:33:25,499 --> 01:33:28,798
and take as many people with you as possible.

1125
01:33:30,438 --> 01:33:33,805
That's the real reason for planting the bomb.

1126
01:33:35,309 --> 01:33:36,139
Are you stupid?

1127
01:33:36,777 --> 01:33:39,143
You don't have a clue how I feel.

1128
01:33:39,347 --> 01:33:41,474
You're the one without a clue.

1129
01:33:42,717 --> 01:33:45,515
Why did innocent people have to die?

1130
01:33:45,886 --> 01:33:49,947
All you care about is your mother.

1131
01:33:50,157 --> 01:33:53,649
Why did Manami and Kitahara have to die?

1132
01:33:53,961 --> 01:33:55,428
It doesn't matter who I kill.

1133
01:33:55,630 --> 01:33:57,825
Then just kill your beloved mother.

1134
01:33:58,032 --> 01:33:59,192
Shut up!

1135
01:33:59,600 --> 01:34:01,465
Give that to me.

1136
01:34:10,611 --> 01:34:13,580
The police will be there soon.

1137
01:34:14,081 --> 01:34:16,948
Should've discovered Kitahara's body about now.

1138
01:34:18,519 --> 01:34:19,349
That poor kid...

1139
01:34:20,521 --> 01:34:22,455
She was the only one,

1140
01:34:23,024 --> 01:34:25,117
who knew what an arrogant weakling you are.

1141
01:34:25,559 --> 01:34:28,255
It's just a minor committing murder.

1142
01:34:28,529 --> 01:34:32,158
The penal code will protect me.
I won't get the death sentence.

1143
01:34:32,466 --> 01:34:34,696
Even if the law protects you,

1144
01:34:35,302 --> 01:34:37,532
I will never forgive.

1145
01:34:42,209 --> 01:34:44,177
This morning, after dismantling your bomb.

1146
01:34:46,347 --> 01:34:48,713
I went to see someone.

1147
01:34:50,217 --> 01:34:52,185
Taking with me,

1148
01:34:52,486 --> 01:34:54,147
your precious present.

1149
01:35:12,773 --> 01:35:15,799
This person that you'd been longing to see,

1150
01:35:16,010 --> 01:35:18,808
I was able to meet easily.

1151
01:35:20,281 --> 01:35:23,307
Apparently, she'd only just
returned from her honeymoon.

1152
01:35:28,322 --> 01:35:30,882
We talked about everything.

1153
01:35:31,158 --> 01:35:33,888
I told her how much you loved her.

1154
01:35:34,261 --> 01:35:37,355
How many had been sacrificed.

1155
01:35:38,199 --> 01:35:39,860
It turns out,

1156
01:35:40,701 --> 01:35:43,295
she'd not forgotten you at all.

1157
01:35:44,371 --> 01:35:45,235
Stop it.

1158
01:35:48,776 --> 01:35:52,303
At the very least, I gave her your present.

1159
01:35:53,848 --> 01:35:56,282
I dropped off your invention.

1160
01:35:57,218 --> 01:35:59,618
Then quickly said my goodbyes.

1161
01:36:29,617 --> 01:36:31,812
Your mother's a lovely woman.

1162
01:36:32,052 --> 01:36:35,453
So I prayed you wouldn't push the button.

1163
01:36:39,393 --> 01:36:40,485
But in the end...

1164
01:36:44,665 --> 01:36:45,859
...you went ahead.

1165
01:36:49,470 --> 01:36:50,937
Just kidding.

1166
01:36:59,246 --> 01:37:03,546
I heard the sound of
an important thing disappearing, too.

1167
01:37:06,620 --> 01:37:08,485
Not so much, "pop"...

1168
01:37:10,624 --> 01:37:12,023
...as "Boom!"

1169
01:37:20,901 --> 01:37:22,960
Shut up!

1170
01:41:34,855 --> 01:41:35,844
Mr. Watanabe,

1171
01:41:36,690 --> 01:41:40,649
the bomb was built and was activated

1172
01:41:40,861 --> 01:41:42,192
by you.

1173
01:42:25,606 --> 01:42:28,040
This is my revenge.

1174
01:42:31,945 --> 01:42:33,412
A living hell.

1175
01:42:50,030 --> 01:42:51,588
From now on,

1176
01:42:52,799 --> 01:42:56,860
your reformation begins, one step at a time.

1177
